p South of the United States around the 1860s. It uses call-and-response patterns, blue notes, and the twelve-bar harmonic structure, influencing nearly all modern American music.", "Funk is a music genre that originated in African-American communities in the mid-1960s, emphasizing groove, syncopated basslines, and rhythmic drumming. James Brown, Parliament-Funkadelic, and Earth, Wind & Fire are foundational artists.", "R&B, or rhythm and blues, is a genre of popular music that originated in African-American communities in the 1940s. It blends soulful vocals with funk and pop influences, with modern artists like Beyonc\u00c3\u00a9, Usher, and Alicia Keys.", "Soul music is a genre that originated in African-American communities in the United States during the 1950s and 1960s. It combines gospel vocal style with rhythm and blues, with legends like Aretha Franklin, Ray Charles, and Marvin Gaye."], "scores": [0.9284023048264926, 0.8539013692378243, 0.8490369688373968, 0.8483323087722127, 0.8391988516945033], "model_name": "gte-small", "document_ids": ["Jazz", "Blues", "Funk", "R&B", "Soul"]}}